## Non-Negotiable Rules

Advisory reminders — Gemini has no blocking-hook runtime in this bundle, so discipline matters.

- **No AI attribution anywhere** — never mention AI, Gemini, agent names, or TDD phases in
  commits, PR descriptions, code comments, documentation, or any project artefact. No
  `Co-Authored-By` trailers, no `Generated with` footers.
- **No hardcoded secrets** — environment variables only; fail-fast if absent; never log secrets.
- **No `print()` in library code** (Python) / **no `console.log` in `src/`** (TypeScript) —
  structured logging only.
- **No bare `except:`** (Python) — catch specific exceptions.
- **Parameterised SQL only** — no string interpolation with user input.
- **Coverage floors** — ≥95% Python, ≥80% TypeScript, on all changed files.

---

## Commit Standard (Conventional Commits)

Format: `{type}({scope}): {description}` — types: `feat` `fix` `refactor` `test` `docs` `chore`.
Breaking change: add `!` before `:`. Never mention TDD phases, agent names, or AI.

---

## Branch Rules

**NEVER commit directly to `main` / `master`. Always use a feature branch.** One branch per
logical unit of work; open a PR that passes CI before merging; delete the branch after merge.

---

## Agents

Invoke agents with `@<name>`. The 14 shipped Gemini agents live in `agents/gemini/`:

`ai-developer`, `architect`, `coder`, `coder-python`, `coder-sql`, `coder-tdd`,
`coder-typescript`, `data-analyst`, `jira-story`, `observability`, `product-owner`,
`reviewer`, `security`, `sre`.

Skills are shared from `skills/` — read the relevant `SKILL.md` on demand.
